        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1782101373
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13695#discussion_r3449628046\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>IIRC you were thinking this might be const-<code>false</code>, did that not end up being the case?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 605568240,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1782101373
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13695#discussion_r3449621814\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I realize this is preexisting, but is there an issue on file and/or could you file an issue for deduplicating all this? This seems pretty verbose, duplicative, and error-prone if we have refactorings in the future. I'd love to move towards a world where <code>VMContext</code> and/or <code>VMOffsets</code> is largely defined by a macro for example which could perhaps help a lot here. I don't have any idea how we'd do that, though, and I don't want to block this, but I think it'd be good to track this in an issue.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 605568241,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1782101373
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13695#discussion_r3449637596\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Could this include some small notes/references to how this is implemented in a dual of CLIF-generated code + the libcall itself?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 605568242,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1782101373
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13695#discussion_r3449734823\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Mind going through these tests and trimming down these comments? I suspect most of these can be shortened to just decribing what the test is doing</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 605568243,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1782101373
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13695#discussion_r3449670900\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Perhaps <code>Option&lt;VmPtr&lt;VMDeferredThread&gt;&gt;</code> to juggle provenance?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 605568244,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1782101374
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13695#discussion_r3449645320\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Like above, could this have a comment as well?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 605568245,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1782101374
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13695#discussion_r3449640252\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>(not blocking) this is another file where a macro might be able to help reduce all the boilerplate needed here...</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 605568246,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1782101374
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13695#discussion_r3449644685\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Could this have a comment explaining what it's doing?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 605568247,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1782101374
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13695#discussion_r3449675426\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>before I forget about this, can you add notes/docs to enter/exit as-implemented in the <a href=\"http://concurrent.rs\">concurrent.rs</a> file indicating that the implementation is additionally in JIT code and the two should be kept in-sync?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 605568248,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1782101374
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13695#discussion_r3449647436\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Orthogonally (sort of) it's kind of a bummer that a whole new <code>FuncKey</code> is added here when it's basically not used anywhere. Could the \"known imports\" field transition to being a <code>enum { FuncKey, Trampoline }</code> and would that help avoid adding this as a new <code>FuncKey</code> and having to handle it places?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 605568249,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1782101374
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13695#discussion_r3449696216\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>This is a good point, and something that I'm a bit worried about. Calling <code>set_trapped</code> above is not something that memory safety relies on, just correctness. Here however this is load-bearing for memory safety and if we ever forget to do this it's quite bad.</p>\n<p>I'm not confident that this block is hit for every single possible trap in wasm code. Basically I'm worried we have preexisting niche cases that <code>set_trapped</code> doesn't get called today, and those cases are now extending to this. I'm not certain of this, though, because I can't articulate the exact sequence that would lead to this...</p>\n<p>WDYT though about moving this reset to JIT code itself? That should be possible, I believe, from our entry trampolines when concurrency is enabled. Does that sound ok? I'd be a bit more comfortable in accepting that that would catch everything personally. This is a pretty mild preference, though, so feel free to push back.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 605568250,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1782101374
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"thumbs up\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f44d\" role=\"img\" title=\"thumbs up\">:thumbs_up:</span> alexcrichton submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13695#pullrequestreview-4541054255\">PR review</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Actually I'll go ahead and flag this for merge. One thing I'd recommend, if you can, is to get an LLM review locally as well to double-check this signs off with no known bugs. If nothing materially changes from my suggestions/comments though seems fine to land.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 605570024,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1782101705
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> fitzgen submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13695#pullrequestreview-4545794372\">PR review</a>.</p>",
